{
  "stem": "16503.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I always could get a job regardless of language because, if I knew what I was doing, I didn't need a language.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I left in the 1948 just before Christmas.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I left legally from Prague.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's when the communists took over.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I left with my husband.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was not my husband then, but we were going together.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was 8-- just 18.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was a volunteer [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to Israel, and so, well, I went to-- I went with a transport to Israel because that was the only way you could get out at the time.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was supposed to go to Australia before that, but then I met my husband.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when the Australia question came in, I decided I will go to Israel because he was more important to me to go to Israel with him.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was a Czech squadron, and he was a pilot, a trained pilot from Britain.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so he volunteered and, and went into the-- into Israel under the umbrella of a pilot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went under the umbrella of I'm going to Israel to see because I even took a leave of absence for a year from the job.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was working at the dental clinic, and I took a leave of absence only.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in '48.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In December.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they, they were in-- they had the first war that they were-- you know, Israel was declared a state, and, and they were bringing in the, the refugees from all over the world.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the, the Arabs were stopping them everywhere.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we, we went on a, on a passport-- on a Czech-- not like an individual passport, but on a list of Czech emigrants to-- through the Austrian and German border.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
